GIT Reset  :-
Soft Reset :-  delete all commit id without change data in file
 Example :-     
echo "v1" >> v1
git add .
git commit -m  "1"
echo "v1 second " >> v1
git add .
git commit -m "2"
git log v1
echo "v1 thired" >> v1
git add .
git commit -m "3"
echo "v1 foure" >> v1
git add .
git commit -m "4"
clear
git log v1
cat v1
git reset --soft e9b7e98ded63
cat v1
 git log v1
----- Hard reset--
Commit id and data all will be deleted
$ git reset --hard e9b7e98de
------mixted reset----
]$ git reset --mixed e9b7e98de
